# Foundations

This guide covers `Pathogen::*` components, Lookbook previews, and how host apps should use them. Feature specs can link here and note any local exceptions in a sentence or two.

## Who owns what

- **Pathogen** — shared components, tokens, and previews.
- **Host apps** — brand mapping and product-specific layout; reusable UI should land in Pathogen when multiple apps need it.
- **Previews** — should look like the product, not like a marketing site.

## Principles we keep coming back to

**Form follows workflow.** If a visual choice doesn't help someone understand structure, state, or what to do next, drop it.

**Less, but better.** One confident primary action, calm type, flat surfaces, and small hits of colour beat expressive layout.

**It should feel obvious.** A control ought to look like the natural answer to the task — not like decoration added at the end.

**Details matter even when hidden.** Focus rings, tab order, ARIA labels, and disabled behaviour are design work.

## Building blocks

Pathogen UI is built from a small set of repeatable pieces. Reuse them; don't fork parallel styles.

This section matches the **tokens → building blocks** layers in the [overview diagram](<%= page_path("design-system-overview") %>). Start with intent, then work through colour, type, spacing, corners, elevation, and motion.

### 1. Intent

Before picking classes, name the job: primary action, cancel, status, navigation, metadata, destructive confirm. Intent picks tone, emphasis, colour role, and where the control sits.

### 2. Colour

Use semantic roles (`--pvc-color-*`), not one-off palette stops (`primary-600`, `slate-200`) in shared components.

| Family | For |
|--------|-----|
| Surface / muted / raised | Backgrounds and layering |
| Border / border-strong | Edges, dividers, table rules |
| Text / text-muted | Body and secondary copy |
| Accent (+ strong, solid, solid-hover) | Brand actions, links, selection |
| Danger (+ strong, solid, solid-hover) | Destructive actions and error state |
| Success / warning | Status text, borders, icons (solid fills not ready yet — see [token list](<%= page_path("design-system-tokens") %>#whats-on-our-list)) |
| Focus | Keyboard focus — fixed hue, separate from accent ([focus](#focus-and-keyboard)) |

Accent and danger each have a full **four-step ladder**: foreground pair for text and outlines, solid pair for filled buttons. Success and warning are **base-only** for now — don't fake a solid success button with raw `emerald-700`; wait for the ladder on the token list.

Host apps theme accent via `--color-primary-*`. Shared components shouldn't hard-code IRIDA green or Pathogen blue.

**Still migrating:** `Button` and `CopyableValue` use semantic roles. Typography, Link, Tabs, Form, and Tooltip still mix in `neutral-*` / `primary-*` in places — touch those files toward `--pvc-color-*` when you can.

### 3. Typography

| Role | Token / class | Typical use |
|------|---------------|-------------|
| Meta | `--type-meta` / `text-xs` | Hints, timestamps, grid footnotes |
| Control | `--type-control` / `text-sm` | Labels, buttons, dense UI |
| Body | `--type-body` / `text-base` | Paragraphs, descriptions |
| Section | `--type-section` / `text-xl` | Section titles |
| Page | `--type-page` / `text-3xl`+ | Page titles via `Heading` |

**14px and 16px** do most of the work. Go larger only for real hierarchy.

- Labels for settings and rows: `text-sm font-semibold`.
- Muted copy: `--pvc-color-text-muted` or typography `muted`.
- Weights stay calm: normal body, semibold labels — save extrabold for top-level headings.
- Page titles live in `Pathogen::Typography::Heading`; hosts shouldn't override them.
- `Eyebrow` is the one routine uppercase label; don't sprinkle display type elsewhere.

Prefer `text-[length:var(--type-control)]` in new code. Existing `text-sm` is fine where it matches the token.

### 4. Spacing

Base unit: **4px** (Tailwind default).

| Step | Class | Good for |
|------|-------|----------|
| 4px | `gap-1`, `space-y-1` | Tight groups, icon padding |
| 8px | `gap-2`, `space-y-2` | Inside controls, compact stacks |
| 16px | `gap-4`, `space-y-4` | Forms, fieldsets |
| 24px | `gap-6` | Between sections |
| 32px | `gap-8` | Between major regions |

Line labels, columns, and action groups up to the same grid. Skip custom page spacing unless a component absorbs a repeated pattern.

### 5. Corner radius

| Token | Size | Use on |
|-------|------|--------|
| `--pvc-radius-control-sm` | 2px | Checkboxes |
| `--pvc-radius-control` | 4px | Inputs, inline code |
| `--pvc-radius-action` | 6px | Buttons, tabs |
| `--pvc-radius-panel` | 8px | Grids, grouped panels |

Sharper corners suit dense clinical UI. Skip `rounded-xl` on everyday surfaces. Pills (`rounded-full`) are for radios, switches, and avatars — not general panels.

<span id="elevation"></span>

### 6. Elevation

| Level | How |
|-------|-----|
| Base | Border + surface colour, no shadow |
| Grouped | Muted surface or stronger border — still no shadow |
| Overlay | `--pvc-shadow-overlay` for tooltips, popovers, menus |

We only have two shadow tokens on purpose: product UI stays flat; only floating layers cast shadow. See [Rams in the overview](<%= page_path("design-system-overview") %>) — borders before shadows.

No `shadow-lg` in product examples.

### 7. Motion

| Token | Duration | Use |
|-------|----------|-----|
| `--pvc-duration-fast` | 120ms | Control colour and border |
| `--pvc-duration-default` | 160ms | General feedback |
| `--pvc-duration-overlay` | 200ms | Tooltips, popovers |

Animate colour, border, background, and opacity before position. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Surfaces

A **surface** is a bounded region: panel, grid, fieldset, dialog body, preview frame.

Recipe:

- Background: `--pvc-color-surface` or `--pvc-color-surface-muted`
- Border: 1px `--pvc-color-border`
- Radius: `--pvc-radius-panel` for large frames; `--pvc-radius-control` for fields
- Shadow only if it's an overlay

`DataGridComponent` is our main framed surface today. Hosts can compose the same recipe from tokens until we add a shared `Panel` component.

## Layout

- **Grid first** — columns and dividers show real structure.
- **Asymmetry when the workflow is asymmetric** — primary column wider because the task demands it, not because it looks editorial.
- **Room to breathe in dense UI** — leave space for focus rings and validation text.
- **Structure before icons and colour blocks** — label → control → help → action often looks good enough on its own.

Think GitHub, Linear, public-sector data tools — not landing pages.

## Using colour

- Neutrals hold the room.
- Accent moves work forward.
- Status colours mean something (danger, warning, success) — not mood.
- Big colour fields stay small: selected row, active tab, focus ring, badge.

Skip gradient shells and violet feature blocks that don't encode state.

## Buttons

Two knobs: **tone** (meaning) and **emphasis** (visual weight).

| | Values |
|---|--------|
| `tone` | `neutral`, `primary`, `danger` |
| `emphasis` | `solid`, `outline`, `ghost` (heaviest → lightest) |

Legacy `scheme` still maps: `default` → neutral outline, `primary` → primary solid, `danger` → danger outline.

See Button **Overview** and **Accessibility** previews for real examples.

### Picking tone + emphasis

Read each tone as the same weight scale with different meaning:

**Primary** — `solid` main action · `outline` secondary brand action · `ghost` quiet tertiary

**Neutral** — `solid` rare strong neutral · `outline` cancel/close · `ghost` toolbars and utilities

**Danger** — `solid` confirmed delete only · `outline` destructive with confirm elsewhere · `ghost` dense destructive utility

### Placement

- One `primary` + `solid` per action group.
- Form footers: primary action last; cancel secondary.
- Toolbars: `small`, `ghost` or `outline`, named icon buttons.

### Hover on solid buttons

Solid fills should **darken** on hover, not lighten — like pressing further in. Danger already does this (`red-600` → `red-700`). Primary currently lightens on hover; that's on the [token fix list](<%= page_path("design-system-tokens") %>#whats-on-our-list), not intentional.

### Size and state

| Size | Where | Min target |
|------|-------|------------|
| `medium` | Forms, dialogs | 44px |
| `small` | Toolbars, grids | 24px, **8px gap between neighbours** |

Short verb labels. Icon-only needs `aria-label` or visible text. Use `disabled` when unfocusable; `aria_disabled` when you still need focus for validation feedback.

Use `Pathogen::Link` for inline navigation; button-styled links only inside button groups.

## Links

`Pathogen::Link` — underlined inline navigation with accent on hover. Not for toolbar actions (use buttons).

## Forms

- Native controls first.
- Labels: `text-sm font-semibold`, `--pvc-color-text`.
- Fieldsets: `gap-4`.
- Checkboxes: `--pvc-radius-control-sm`. Radios/switches: `rounded-full`.
- Prefer `PathogenFormBuilder` and `Pathogen::Form::*`.

## Data grid

Dense surface. Dark mode may use `neutral-950` **inside the grid frame** only — not as the app background. See [dark mode](<%= page_path("design-system-dark-mode") %>).

Keep hover, focus, selected, and disabled visibly different.

<span id="focus-and-keyboard"></span>

## Focus and keyboard

Focus must show in light, dark, high-contrast, and forced-colours modes — and stay distinct from accent colour.

`--pvc-color-focus` should stay **fixed** (`primary-500` in both modes) so rings don't blend into accent text. Dark mode currently ships `primary-400` (same as accent) — on the [token list](<%= page_path("design-system-tokens") %>#whats-on-our-list) to fix.

**Default pattern:** `focus-visible:outline-2 outline-[var(--pvc-color-focus)] outline-offset-2`

`Button` and `CopyableValue` use this. Link, Tabs, and Form may still use black/white outlines — fine for now; converge on `--pvc-color-focus` when you touch them.

Don't hide focus with transparent borders. Don't rely on colour alone for state.

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML.
- WCAG AA contrast.
- Visible focus.
- Screen-reader names that match what people see.
- Reduced motion for non-essential animation.
- Forced-colours support on custom controls.

## When to bend the rules

Sometimes the workflow genuinely needs a different pattern. Say what you broke, why, and whether it should become a shared component or token. Undocumented one-offs pile up fast.
